<font color="#FF0000">MEDALS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jan 12 14:24:09 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
The mention of medals seems to be a waste of time. I know of no other vet on this site mentioning what awards they have recieved. Sounds like posturing to me. I served in the 1st Cav in 1969 and we knew when we were in Cambodia. I recieved a silver star, two bronze stars and air medals with V device which tells me that those on &quot;unmentionable&quot; missions DID recieve what was due. I knew of no one who was denied medals not earned while in Cambodia.<br><br>
The talk of medals earned while incountry, seems classless. Sounds like the full bird who took a fly over a combat situation, for five minutes and awarded himself the silver star.
<p><code>--   (a vet) </code><p>


